  Minor caveats

  • The ask tool necessarily pauses for an answer; for this self-test I used
    it in a harmless way and proceeded.
  batch reports success compactly; if you need the detailed payload from each
  call, separate direct calls can be easier to inspect.
  • I did not test agent_kill because it’s a cancellation path rather than a
    normal success path, and there was no need to interrupt a running child.

  Bottom line

  • Yes: the tools work well overall.
  • The local file, shell, edit, orchestration, delegation, and web flows all
    behaved as expected in this test.

